│ the Issue: The crash occurs due to a PHI node verification failure after    │
│ loop fusion. The error message shows that `%sum1.0.lcssa = phi i32 [ %add,  │
│ %for.inc ]` has predecessors `label %for.inc` and `label %for.inc6`, but    │
│ the PHI only lists one predecessor (`%for.inc`). This indicates that during │
│ loop fusion, the exit block of the first loop (which contains the LCSSA     │
│ PHI) is being modified incorrectly, causing it to have additional           │
│ predecessors without updating the PHI node accordingly.\n\n2. Analyzing     │
│ `opt`'s Log: The log shows that the fusion is attempted between two loops   │
│ with preheaders `entry` and `for.end`. The first loop exits to `for.end`,   │
│ which serves as the preheader for the second loop. During fusion, the code  │
│ attempts to remove the preheader of the second loop (`for.end`) by          │
│ replacing its terminator with an UnreachableInst. However, the LCSSA PHI    │
│ node `%sum1.0.lcssa` in `for.end` still exists and now has incorrect        │
│ predecessor information because the block is being repurposed as part of    │
│ the fused loop structure.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The issue stems from   │
│ line 1655-1657 in `performFusion()`. The code assumes that `FC1.Preheader`  │
│ (which is `for.end` in this case) is empty and can be safely replaced with  │
│ an UnreachableInst. However, `for.end` contains the LCSSA PHI node          │
│ `%sum1.0.lcssa` that is needed for correct SSA form. When the preheader is  │
│ eliminated without properly handling these PHI nodes, the resulting IR      │
│ becomes invalid. The assertion at line 1760 catches this malformed PHI node │
│ during function verification.\n\nThe problem is that the code doesn't       │
│ account for the fact that the exit block of the first loop (which becomes   │
│ the preheader of the second loop) may contain LCSSA PHI nodes that need to  │
│ be preserved or properly updated during fusion.\n\n4. Proposed Edit         │
│ Point(s): The fix needs to handle LCSSA PHI nodes in the preheader block    │
│ before eliminating it. Specifically, we need to check if the preheader      │
│ contains any PHI nodes and either:\n   - Move them to an appropriate        │
│ location, or\n   - Update their predecessor information correctly\n   - Or  │
│ avoid eliminating the block if it contains essential PHI nodes\n\nHowever,  │
│ looking more carefully at the code flow, the real issue is that the exit    │
│ block of the first loop (`FC0.ExitBlock`) and the preheader of the second   │
│ loop (`FC1.Preheader`) are the same block (as confirmed by debugger:        │
│ `FC0.ExitBlock == FC1.Preheader` is true). This block contains the LCSSA    │
│ PHI node `%sum1.0.lcssa`. The current code tries to eliminate this block by │
│ replacing its terminator with UnreachableInst, but this destroys the PHI    │
│ node that's still needed.\n\nThe correct approach is to recognize that when │
│ `FC0.ExitBlock == FC1.Preheader`, we cannot simply eliminate the preheader  │
